# 🎯 TALENT-IQ — Complete Interview Q&A

> Covers every part of the project: architecture, backend, frontend, real-time, AI, code execution, auth, email, deployment, and design decisions.

---

## 📐 Section 1: Project Overview & Architecture

### Q1. What is TALENT-IQ and what problem does it solve?
**A:** TALENT-IQ is a **real-time collaborative coding interview platform**. It solves the problem of conducting technical interviews remotely by combining:
- A shared code editor (both users type simultaneously and see each other's changes)
- A live video call + text chat in the same window
- A curated set of LeetCode-style problems
- AI-powered code review after submission
- Email notifications for session events

### Q2. What is the overall architecture of the project?
**A:** The project is a **full-stack monorepo** with three distinct layers:

| Layer | Tech | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| **Frontend** | React + Vite | SPA served at `/`, handles UI, routing, real-time collab |
| **Backend** | Node.js + Express | REST API, auth middleware, DB operations, external SDKs |
| **Database** | MongoDB (Mongoose) | Persists Sessions and Users |

External services integrated:
- **Clerk** → Authentication
- **Stream** → Video calls + chat messaging
- **Yjs + y-webrtc** → Real-time collaborative code editing (P2P)
- **Groq (LLaMA 3.3 70B)** → AI code review
- **Judge0** → Remote code execution
- **Inngest** → Background event-driven functions (webhooks)
- **Nodemailer + Gmail SMTP** → Transactional email

### Q3. How is the project deployed?
**A:**
- **Frontend** is built with Vite and the dist is served statically by the Express backend in **production** (`express.static` pointing to `../frontend/dist`).
- A [vercel.json](file:///c:/Users/aksha/OneDrive/Desktop/TALENT-IQ/vercel.json) exists at both root and frontend level, indicating Vercel is also used as a possible deployment target.
- In development, the frontend Vite dev server and the backend Express server run separately.

